        <h2>How we disclose your information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p><strong>When you tell us to.</strong> When you add your content to the services, you are telling us to make that content available to certain people or communities. Who can access that information is determined by who can access a particular space. For courses, those permissions are set by course owners or admins. They control whether a course requires an invite link or is open and accessible to anyone. And these permissions, like the size of the course, may change over time. Similarly, if you link your iShariu account with a third-party service (like a music-streaming service or gaming platform), embed content, interact with third party content posted on iShariu, or participate in a course that has third-party features like bots enabled, we may provide certain information to that service or to other iShariu users to operate that service or feature. Additionally, if you purchase goods or services from other users on iShariu, we may disclose certain information to these users in order to facilitate the delivery of the goods or services purchased or help them understand and improve their business. We may also disclose your information as you otherwise instruct us or provide us your consent to do so.</p>
